<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="252" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                    <head>Teachers of the Ragged School</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 1, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Honored Sir</hi>: We, the undersigned, teachers
                        connected with the Bristol ragged schools, beg permission to express through
                        you our unqualified indignation at the brutal act which has deprived America
                        of one of its best Presidents, and of the man especially adapted to the
                        requirements of the time.</p>
                    <p>We venture to ask that you will kindly forward our condolence to Mrs.
                        Lincoln, who has been so barbarously bereaved of her illustrious
                        husband.</p>
                    <pb facs="0238" n="166" xml:id="pg_166"/>
                    <p>We earnestly pray that God will speedily restore peace to your united and
                        great country, and rescue it from the effects of a most wanton and wicked
                        rebellion.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>JAMES SHEPPERLY, <hi rend="italic">Master</hi>.</item>
                                <item>MARTHA JANE HARWOOD, <hi rend="italic">Infant
                                    Mistress</hi>.</item>
                                <item>JOHN ALLEN.</item>
                                <item>ELIZA OXBURGH.</item>
                                <item>LOUISA COOK.</item>
                                <item>RICHARD WEYMAN, <hi rend="italic">Tailor</hi>.</item>
                                <item>ELIZA PALMER.</item>
                                <item>JOSEPH PALMER.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">C. F. Adams</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">United States Minister</hi>.</p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>